Package enums

package enums
Enumeration types for the Internship Placement Management System.

This package contains all type-safe enumeration classes that define fixed sets of constants used throughout the application. Enums provide compile-time type safety and prevent invalid values.

Enumerations:

User-Related:

  • UserRole - System roles (STUDENT, COMPANY_REPRESENTATIVE, CAREER_CENTER_STAFF)
  • Major - Academic majors (CSC, EEE, MAE, etc.)

Internship-Related:

  • InternshipLevel - Internship difficulty levels (BASIC, INTERMEDIATE, ADVANCED)
  • InternshipStatus - Internship states (DRAFT, PENDING_APPROVAL, APPROVED, FILLED)

Application invalid input: '&' Approval:

  • ApplicationStatus - Application states (PENDING, SUCCESSFUL, REJECTED, WITHDRAWN)
  • ApprovalStatus - Approval workflow states (PENDING_APPROVAL, APPROVED, REJECTED)

All enums include helper methods for validation and conversion, ensuring data integrity throughout the application.

Since:
1.0.0
Author:
